---
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
import SiteLayout from "../components/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Testimonials"
  description="Verbatim client and partner feedback used as supporting proof alongside case studies and evidence documents."
  pathname="/testimonials"
  crumbs={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "Testimonials" }]}
>
  <PageHeader
    title="Testimonials and <em>recommendation context</em>."
    subtitle="Short, verbatim feedback from client and partner contexts. This page treats testimonials as <b>supporting evidence</b>, not as the primary basis of the case."
    crumbs={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "Testimonials" }]}
  />

  <section class="section wrap first" data-screen-label="Testimonials">
    <div class="tst-counter rv">
      <div class="stat"><span class="v"><em>4</em></span><span class="k">Verbatim quotes</span></div>
      <div class="stat"><span class="v">12<em>+</em></span><span class="k">Named client programmes</span></div>
      <div class="stat"><span class="v">11<em>+</em></span><span class="k">Verticals served</span></div>
    </div>

    <div class="tst-grid">
      <article class="tst tst-quote size-lg rv" data-tilt>
        <span class="tst-tag">★ BBC · Media · UK</span>
        <p class="body">The tool is working fully, and we’ve been able to <b>share the update with wider teams</b>.</p>
        <div class="tst-sig">
          <div class="tst-sig-l"><span class="name">BBC</span><span class="role">Project stakeholder</span></div>
          <span class="tst-sig-r">Media · UK</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="tst tst-letter size-md rv d1" data-tilt>
        <span class="tst-stamp">Verbatim</span>
        <span class="tst-tag">General Mills · Blue Buffalo</span>
        <p class="body">The feedback was very positive… overall they are happy with the first go at this. I appreciate all your help and of course <b>passed on high praise of your work</b>.</p>
        <div class="tst-sig">
          <div class="tst-sig-l"><span class="name">General Mills</span><span class="role">Account team · Blue Buffalo</span></div>
          <span class="tst-sig-r">Consumer · global</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="tst tst-framed size-md rv d2" data-tilt>
        <span class="tst-tag">Diligent Pharma</span>
        <p class="body">Our analytics are <b>in great shape</b> at this point and we’re feeling confident about the ways they will help us.</p>
        <div class="tst-sig">
          <div class="tst-sig-l"><span class="name">Diligent Pharma</span><span class="role">Stakeholder</span></div>
          <span class="tst-sig-r">Pharma · life sciences</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="tst tst-quote size-md rv d3" data-tilt>
        <span class="tst-tag">★ MRI Management</span>
        <p class="body">I really liked working with you and hope we can build a working relationship. <b>I have 3 to 4 clients that require your skills on a routine basis</b>.</p>
        <div class="tst-sig">
          <div class="tst-sig-l"><span class="name">MRI Management</span><span class="role">Engagement partner</span></div>
          <span class="tst-sig-r">Property tech · US</span>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="rv" style="margin-top:48px;padding:18px 22px;background:rgba(200,153,66,.12);border:1px solid rgba(200,153,66,.4);border-radius:14px;font-size:14px;color:var(--ink-2);line-height:1.55">
      <b style="color:var(--ink);font-weight:600">These quotes support the broader case; they do not replace it.</b> The main proof remains the combination of role context, shipped systems, publications, recognition, and supporting evidence. See <a href="/evidence" style="color:var(--terra);border-bottom:1px solid currentColor">the evidence route</a> for the wider proof structure.
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
